The Silver Hand

Thieves' Guild

Influence: Realm wide

Purpose: A network dedicated to acquiring wealth, power and influence through covert means. They balance their criminal activities with maintaining order in the realms.
Beliefs: Honor among thieves, Loyalty and discretion.
Leader: Lysandra "Silverfist" Valen (Strategic General) Symbol: A silver handprint
Headquarters: The Veiled Palm in Sentinel's Rest
Current Goal: Expand Territory & Accumulate Wealth Allies: The Shieldhaven Academy
Enemies:

Traits: Dabbles in forbidden magic

Tasks:

  • Secure a powerful artifact

Relationships to other Factions:

  • Is at war with The Silver Hand
  • Is strongly allied with The Shieldhaven Academy

Locations

The Veiled Palm

The Sword District in Sentinel's Rest

The Veiled Palm is a high-end brothel run by Mistress Mira. If you know the secret password, you are admitted below into The Embrace which is the headquarters for The Silver Hand.

Lysandra "Silverfist" Valen

Lysandra Valen was formerly an assassin of great renown before she became the leader of The Silver Hand. Lysandra earned her nick name "Silverfist" from her favored weapon -- a pair of silvered gauntlets with hidden blades.

Lysandra seized the opportunity to eliminate an internal faction and their weakened leader after the internal faction tried a coup and failed. She used the distraction and the advantage to gain herself the thrown in one quick and decisive action.

Lysandra is fierce, charming and intelligent. She is ruthless in her pursuit for power, but she values loyalty and competence, rewarding those who prove their worth and eliminating those who fail her.

As an orphan herself Lysandra builds strong ties with The Shieldhaven Academy -- the place she grew up and was taught everything she knew.

Lysandra has raven black hair that falls to her shoulders. Her eyes are sharp and the color of newly grown grass. She is tall for a Smallfolk.

tov-monster-vault-6-12-24, p.364

Mistress Mira

Mistress Mira and most of her employees are well trained spies. They use their assets to garner information that would be of use to The Silver Hand.
